                        "created_at": "1770729715",
                        "id": "17954855934069431",
                        "text": "\ud83d\uddfcCan I complete 50 Tokyo Bucket List items in 5 days!?\n\nTokyo has SO much to offer that it can get super overwhelming- even as someone who\u2019s lived here 3.5 years! So I\u2019m challenging myself to explore more and got help from TOMOGO! and Yuko organised everything for Day 1 \ud83d\ude0a\n\nThese are the things on my bucket list and where Yuko ended up taking me \ud83c\udfc3\ud83c\udffb\u200d\u2642\ufe0f\n\n1. yummy bakery: le Bage\n2. unique workshop experience: FUTO\n3. traditional Japan: Kuramae Shrine\n4. local hidden gem restaurant: Tempura Iseya\n5. Japanese stationery: mt lab\n6. pottery & home wares: proto\n7. *viral* cafe: Dandelion Chocolate Cafe\n\nall 7 spots were brand new to me and I genuinely had such an amazing time!! I truly recommend TOMOGO! for their expertise and guidance to make a day in Tokyo so jam-packed full of new experiences, knowledge and fun \ud83e\udd2d I always get along with my guides and Yuko was exactly like hanging out with a long time friend~\n\nBook your own personalised tour with TOMOGO! They are dedicated to highlighting lesser-known areas, local communities, and businesses \ud83d\udc99\n\n\ud83d\udd17 link in bio or here:\n\nhttps://www.tomogo-travel.com/exclusive-tours/omakase-tokyo\n\n\ud83d\udcb8 SAVE 10% off with promo code EBII10 \ud83d\udcb8\n\n#PR #traveljapan #japantrip #tokyojapan"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
